tools.description:
IMPORTANT: Time ranges must be less than 27 weeks. Split longer periods into multiple calls.

    Find events based on the given query, especially useful for searching by category tags such as 1:1, External, etc.
Use this to find specific events on the current user's calendar. Broader queries are more likely to find events.

It allows searching by attendees, title, time ranges, RSVP status, and tags.

Prefer to use category tags to find events by type, such as 1:1, External, etc instead of searching by title.
Attendee search should be done by calendarId. CalendarId can be found by searching for the person by name using the search_people tool.

If unsure what properties to search for, fallback to searching by title.


Examples:
- INVALID: more than 27 weeks
{
  "timeRangeSearch": {
    "includeRanges": [
      {
        "startTime": "2025-01-01T00:00:00Z",
        "endTime": "2025-08-01T00:00:00Z"
      }
    ]
  }
}
- VALID: less than 27 weeks
{
  "timeRangeSearch": {
    "includeRanges": [
      {
        "startTime": "2025-01-01T00:00:00Z",
        "endTime": "2025-06-30T00:00:00Z"
      }
    ]
  }
}

Returns:
  FindEventsResponse containing basic info on the matching events

Update an existing proposal; can remove current diffs, or add request to create, update, or cancel events.

In order to update a proposed change from the previous proposal, remove the diff corresponding to that change (by including it in the "removedDiffs" field), and then add a new diff with the desired properties into "addedDiffs"
Example: Changing the title of a previously proposed new event, with diff ID "diff-12345":
{
  "removedDiffs": ["diff-12345"],
  "addedDiffs": [{
    "newEvents": [{ "title": "new title" }]
  }]
}

In order to add an update modification (i.e. an action that modifies events that currently exist on the calendar), add it to "addedDiffs".
Example: Changing the title of an existing event:
{
  "addedDiffs": [{
    "updateRequests": [{
      "eventIds": ["existing-event-id"],
      "updateMutation": { "title": "new title" }
    }]
  }]
}

Adding diffs takes the same input as create_proposal.

Returns a new proposal, based off the existing one.

If there's a previous proposal that has not been confirmed, always try to update that proposal with the new information.
